title: ICE with RPITIT and wrong number of type parameters

labels.name: I-ICE
labels.description: Issue: The compiler panicked, giving an Internal Compilation Error (ICE) ❄️

labels.name: T-compiler
labels.description: Relevant to the compiler team, which will review and decide on the PR/issue.

body:
### Code ```Rust #![feature(return_position_impl_trait_in_trait)] #![allow(incomplete_features)] struct U; trait Foo { fn bar(&self) -> impl Sized; } impl Foo for U { fn bar(&self) {} //~^ ERROR method `bar` has 1 type parameter but its trait declaration has 0 type parameters } fn main() { U.bar(); } ``` ### Error output ``` error[E0049]: method `bar` has 1 type parameter but its trait declaration has 0 type parameters error: internal compiler error: compiler/rustc_middle/src/ty/subst.rs:726:9: type parameter `T/#0` (T/0) out of range when substituting, substs=[] ```
